<br>
South Korean naval forces several months ago engaged in a major gunfight with North Korean naval units with US AWACs and C3I support, plus there has been a growing number of skirmishs between North and South Korean military units.<br>
<br>
Iran is so unstable that the US might not HAVE to take military action against it, so it's in a wait and see mode.<br>
<br>
Right now we're seeing the chessgame, the initial positioning, the jockeying for position and advantage, the actual fighting has not yet fully begun, but that is because we have the luxury of picking the time and place of our choosing.  After the massive demobilization and intense optempo of the Clinton years, our military needs to complete its maintenance cycles on its equipment, rebuild the depleted arsenals, and restock.<br>
<br>
Just because you don't see it in the press or in the news doesn't mean it isn't happening, the trick is to look at apparantly unrelated developments, inconsistancies in what is known, and trying to figure out why the developments might be related or consistant after all.<br>
<br>
As far as 'to the right' or 'to the left', I, for one, have no animus towards those who disagree with me, indeed, I tend to think that I'm just not explaining myself as best I can when people disagree with me than think that there is anything 'wrong' with what they are saying or with who they are, perhaps its the academic in me *shrug*. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulunathreee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lunathreee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mistayn the mindless</span><br>  Posts: 449<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 3:37:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1218.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: History</span><hr size=1> your citizenship shouldn't suddenly change just because of the unproven possibility that you've engaged in certain activities.  do we classify all drug dealers as non-US citizens, even though we're engaging in a so-called War on Drugs?<br>
