<br>
What did the people of Japan do to deserve World War II?  What did the people of Germany do to deserve either world war?  It isn't the *people* who have done much of anything, its the authoritarian governments that have, are, and will be our opponent.  We did not go to war in Afghanistan against the Afghan people, we went to war against the Taliban and Al-Qaida, and once free the Afghan people were rather enthusiastic about the whole affair.  Unfortunately, it is always the people of authoritarian dictatorships who suffer when those dictatorships engage in war, and remember, they started it, not us.<br>
<br>
Right now the main reason why we aren't hitting Iran is because it is becoming apparant that the people of Iran are about to take matters into their own hands and forcefully remove the Islamofascists from power.  If we can accomplish our goals without having to risk the lives of our fighting men and women, so much the better, I doubt you'll disagree that it is better to risk our money than it is to risk our blood if both can achieve the same goals.<br>
<br>
I'll take your silly comments about President Bush as entertainment, and pass on with merely a point that in no recount in which illegal ballots (those cast by convicted felons) are excluded has Gore won Florida, in order for Gore to win, the law has to be broken... and military absentee ballots have to be ignored.  Indeed, even when *all* overvotes are counted as Gore votes (an overvote is where both Bush and Gore were selected) Bush STILL wins the state, of course, assuming that only Gore supporters would be so imbecilic as to be unable to complete a ballot that first graders were able to handle is hardly complimentary to the intelligence of Gore voters, isn't it.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulothraem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lothraem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.delharen.com/images/sword.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 5:50:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1218.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Treason</span><hr size=1> Held without trial. That is the issue. If you have evidence of intent, assistance or involvement, then by all means necessary detain, prosicute and convict. Treason, Murder, Conspiracy, etc against the citizens of America is a crime. Whether they are a citizen tried millitairially or a non-citizen tried criminally... I couldnt care less. Against such an enemy as we see before us, some necessities arrise.<br>
